user_turn_1=This code works on my machine but crashes in production with `Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'city')`. I have no idea what's different.

```javascript
function getShippingZone(order) {
    const city = order.shipping_address.city;
    const zones = {
        "New York": "east",
        "Los Angeles": "west",
        "Chicago": "central",
    };
    return zones[city] || "standard";
}
```
assistant_turn_1=The error tells you exactly what's happening: `order.shipping_address` is `undefined` in production data.

Your code assumes `order.shipping_address` always exists, but in production, some orders likely have no `shipping_address` property. Your local/test data probably always has a complete shipping address, which is why it works there.

**The fix** — use optional chaining to safely access the nested property:

```javascript
function getShippingZone(order) {
    const city = order.shipping_address?.city;
    const zones = {
        "New York": "east",
        "Los Angeles": "west",
        "Chicago": "central",
    };
    return zones[city] || "standard";
}
```

When `shipping_address` is `undefined`, `order.shipping_address?.city` evaluates to `undefined` (instead of throwing), and `zones[undefined]` returns `undefined`, so the function falls through to `"standard"`.

